President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate James L. Taylor as Chief Financial Officer of the Department of Labor. Taylor has nearly thirty years of federal financial management experience and currently serves as Deputy Inspector General for the Department of Homeland Security. He has received awards for excellence in federal financial management and holds a B.A. from Old Dominion University and an MPA from the University of Delaware.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint Woody N. Peterson as Commissioner of the District of Columbia Judicial Nominations Commission. Peterson is a partner at Dickstein Shapiro LLP and specializes in appellate litigation. He has authored numerous briefs in federal and state appellate courts and is a member of the bars of the District of Columbia and Massachusetts. Peterson holds an A.B. from Harvard College and a J.D. from Harvard Law School.